# Steam Deck Compatibility

When editing or reviewing game project files, watch for these common Steam Deck compatibility issues:

## Resolution

1. **Hardcoded resolutions.** Flag any hardcoded resolution like `1920x1080`, `2560x1440`, or `3840x2160` that doesn't account for the Deck's native `1280x800` display. The game should support arbitrary resolutions or at minimum 1280x800 at 16:10 aspect ratio.

2. **Fullscreen assumptions.** If the code assumes exclusive fullscreen, note that Steam Deck runs games in gamescope (a compositing window manager). Borderless windowed fullscreen works best.

## Input

3. **Mouse-only interactions.** Flag `RightMouseButton`, `right_click`, `MouseButton2`, or cursor-dependent UI (drag-and-drop, hover tooltips) without a controller/gamepad alternative. Steam Deck has trackpads but dedicated controller bindings are strongly preferred.

4. **Small click targets.** UI elements smaller than ~44px touch targets are hard to use with trackpad input. Flag hardcoded small button sizes or tiny font sizes (below 16px at 1280x800).

5. **No controller support.** If the project has no Steam Input configuration (`game_actions_*.vdf`) and no gamepad input handling, warn that Steam Deck verification requires controller support.

## Anti-Cheat

6. **Anti-cheat compatibility.** If the project references EasyAntiCheat (EAC), BattlEye, or other anti-cheat systems, note:
   - EAC and BattlEye both support Proton/Linux — but it must be explicitly enabled in the Steamworks Partner site
   - Kernel-level anti-cheat will NOT work under Proton
   - Provide link: https://partner.steamgames.com/doc/steamdeck/proton

## Linux / Proton

7. **Windows-only paths.** Flag hardcoded Windows paths (`C:\`, `%APPDATA%`, `\\`) without Linux equivalents. Save files should use Steam's recommended paths or `ISteamRemoteStorage`.

8. **DirectX-only rendering.** If the project exclusively uses DirectX without Vulkan fallback, note that Proton translates D3D to Vulkan via DXVK, which works but native Vulkan offers better performance on Deck.

9. **External launchers.** Flag references to external launcher executables (separate .exe for updates, splash screens). These break under Proton and are a common Deck verification failure.

## Reference

- Steam Deck compatibility review: https://partner.steamgames.com/doc/steamdeck/compat
- Proton compatibility: https://partner.steamgames.com/doc/steamdeck/proton
- Steam Deck developer resources: https://partner.steamgames.com/doc/steamdeck
